reviews.headline: The only thing that works!!
reviews.comments: If you're suffering from dry cracked lips, this will eliminate it! 3 days, that's it.

reviews.headline: As usual Lanolips is PERFECT!!!
reviews.comments: Amazing product that smells exactly like lemonade! Keeps my lips moisturized and has a nice shimmer to it!

reviews.headline: Best one yet
reviews.comments: I've become a huge Lanolip fan, and have every single one of their products. But since I've gotten this lemonade treatment, it's all i want to use! It's the perfect thickness. Has a little shimmer in it. And actually not that strong of smell! It's my most fave one and the best one yet! 1000/10

reviews.headline: My favourite lip balm
reviews.comments: This is my favourite lip balm. It feels great, adds some shimmer, comes with a lot and a little goes a long way. This cemented me as a lanolips fan. If this lip balm continues to be made I will buy it 'till the end of time! Truly a comfort product.

reviews.headline: No Notes
reviews.comments: This feels similar in viscosity to Vaseline or Aquaphor but more luxurious and silky. I also feel like it keeps my lips hydrated for longer, even after the balm has been rubbed off. The lemon scent is strong but I'm also a known lemon enthusiast, so thats a win for me. I put it on before bed and wake up to soft, moisturized lips. This is the product that turned me into a lifelong Lanolips fan.

reviews.headline: disappointed
reviews.comments: i was so excited to try this!! couldn't squeeze it out of the tube, then couldn't apply without rubbing between my fingers.

reviews.headline: HARD AS A ROCK
reviews.comments: I was so excited to try these, as I have extremely dry lips. I purchased 3 different flavors.  I cannot believe I'm the only 1 to say anything about how hard it is to get product out of the tube...

reviews.headline: Worth the hype!
reviews.comments:
This one is definitely worth the hype. I'm actually surprised how much I really enjoy this one. I am a Chapstick snob. My go to is Aquaphor in the tube not the stick lip version. I do think the Aquaphor lasts longer but this one has such a beautiful finish due to the shimmer, a great smell, and really moisturizes the lips. 

There are some caveats to it so I would take the following into consideration:
-This has natural lemon essence in it and smells good (to me), but it is a lingering scent and can be overpowering. It smells exactly like lemonade. 
-The applicator is very different than what I'm used to because the formula is so thick. The opening of the hole on the applicator is quite large which results in a lot of product coming out and a messy top/lid. 
-This product only works when it is at room temperature do not leave it in your car in the cold. It will be impossible to use.  Warm-up gently between your palms or place in your shirt to get it softened. 

If those things are not a turn off to you, i would highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Forget whatever's trending - this is the one!
reviews.comments: Absolute only thing that ever healed my cracked, dry lips in winter. I go to sleep with this on and finally don't have to scrub my lips daily. All of the other viral products can't hold a candle to this.

reviews.headline: Saved my lips after allergic reaction to toothpaste
reviews.comments: 2 months ago I had an allergic reaction to a new toothpaste that left my lips dry, irritated, peeling and swollen with broken skin at the corners of my mouth (gross, sorry).  Even after changing toothpastes, the dryness and irritation lingered, nothing seemed to work until I found Lanolips. I have been using this along with the 101 ointment everyday for 9 days and this has saved my lips. They are just about back to normal and the sores at the corners are healed. AMAZING products.

reviews.headline: 2nd fave lip treatment
reviews.comments: It's very moisturizing, and works way better than most any other lip balm, but I could do without the shimmer. Flavor is great and doesn't have that kinda Lemon Pledge note to it that lemon-fragranced things can get. One downside is that I feel like there's a very narrow temperature range where it's a good consistency. Like definitely do not put it in your pocket on a hot day or in a hot car and try and use it cuz it will have liquefied and when you try to put it on you'll end up wearing half the tube. (Just for the record, the OG formula Glossier Balm Dot Com is the absolute best because it works well like this does initially but the Glossier has staying power that this doesn't.)

reviews.headline: Long lasting, great scent for summer
reviews.comments: This stuff works great. Smells even better (to me its a not a crazy overpowering smell either). I put it on before i go to bed and i still feel it on my lips when i wake up so it definitely lasts a long time. I dont have to worry about dry lips waking up anymore. It doesn't take much to cover my lips either so i can see this tube lasting me awhile. Only thing I could complain about is this price, but i used a coupon i had on my app so it became much more affordable in my opinion. Very happy with this purchase.

reviews.headline: LOVE LOVE
reviews.comments: I LOVE this product i would recommend buying this as your first purchase from this brand because its a lip treatment & not the 101 oitment but i still LOVE the 101 oitment but def recommend!

reviews.headline: Amazing!!!
reviews.comments:
I have very dry lips and as a result have ended up with a bad habit of chewing on them. I've tried multiple lip balms with none truly resolving the issue and many drying my lips out even more.
THIS one though, I've been applying it for 3 days and my lips look smoother and healthier than they have in years. There is no longer any skin flaking/peeling and my lips still feel nice after the product has worn off

faceoff_positive.comments:
This is a solid lip moisturizer. I don't think it's worth the high price tag. It's sheer and shiny, as well as shimmery [fine shimmer the same color as the rest of the product] on the lips. It has a moderately strong lemon scent, which I find pleasing -but some may find it a little bit reminiscent of house-cleaner products or lemon hand sanitizer. It has a noticeable taste as well- also lemon, which I'm not a big fan of. I find it effective at moisturizing even quite chapped lips- I find it works better than normal chapstick. 
However, I've also tried the lanolips banana balm lip treatment, and personally prefer that for moisturizing. If you want something less sticky, smoother, less pigmented, and lemony- or more for going out while wearing, I'd go with this one. If you want maximum moisturizing and don't care as much about aesthetics/ are going to use it as a sleeping treatment, I'd pick the banana balm. 
Overall a solid product that I'm not going to return, but overpriced. I'd recommend the lanolips banana balm over this.
faceoff_positive.headline: Nice

faceoff_negative.comments: This was a little bit of a splurge for a basic lip gloss but I'm obsessed with anything lemonade. I wasn't impressed with the moisturizing factor. Didn't do much so I wouldn't go as far as calling this a "lip treatment". It smells wonderful, not overwhelming but noticeable. I wish it tasted as sweet as it smelled. So, here's where the issue comes into play. If this is exposed to ANY type of temperature rise, it becomes a mess. It becomes straight liquid (no viscosity) and the shimmer/formula separates in the tube. Good luck getting it on without it spilling on your hands and/or face. It has a fairly large opening on the applicator which doesn't help the situation. I can consciously be very careful squeezing and it still spills everywhere. If you want to give this gloss a shot, be sure to leave it at home in the air conditioning. Doesn't suit my lifestyle.
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointing
